{"slug":"sirkuler-25-0615eng-1","reference":"Sirkuler_25_0615ENG","gazette":"White House","title":"Changes Made to U.S. Reciprocal Tariff Rates","date":"01 Ağustos 2025","bodyHtml":"<p>U.S. President Trump has signed an Executive Order amending the additional tariff rates based on the principle of reciprocity.</p><p>The rate for Turkey has been increased from 10% to 15%.</p><p>The changes will take effect as of August 7, 2025. For goods loaded or in transit before this date, the previous rate will apply if the import declaration is submitted by October 5, 2025.</p><p>The additional tariffs will continue not to apply to products already subject to sectoral additional duties (e.g., steel, aluminum, copper, automotive, etc.).</p><p>For countries not listed in Annex I of the Executive Order, the additional tariff rate will remain at 10%.</p><p>The situation regarding China is expected to be clarified on August 11–12.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.whitehouse.gov/presidential-actions/2025/07/further-modifying-the-reciprocal-tariff-rates/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"text-decoration-line: underline; font-weight: bold;\">Click here to view the Executive Order.</a></p><p class=\"has-text-align-center\" style=\"text-wrap: pretty; text-align: center; margin-block: 30.9744px 0px; max-width: 808.024px; color: rgb(41, 51, 64); font-family: &quot;Instrument Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 18.6768px; letter-spacing: 0.2px; margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><strong>ANNEX I</strong></p><figure class=\"wp-block-table\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-x: auto; --wh--block--table--padding: 12px; margin-block: 30.9744px 0px; max-width: 808.024px; color: rgb(41, 51, 64); font-family: &quot;Instrument Sans&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 18.6768px; letter-spacing: 0.2px; margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\" style=\"width: 808.013px; table-layout: fixed; border-color: rgb(41, 51, 64) !important;\"><t